quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  52,32,"Do their minds<sup>12</sup> prompt them to say such things, or are they transgressing people?","[12] The leaders of pagans in Makkah claimed to be of great minds. Here it questions their intelligence, arguing that a man cannot be a madman and a poet at the same time."
  52,33,"Or do they say, “He has made this [Qur’an] up”? Rather, they are not willing to believe.",""
  52,34,"Then let them produce a discourse like this, if they are truthful<sup>13</sup>.","[13] Arab pagans were challenged to produce the like of this Quran, ten surahs, or one surah, but the challenge has never been met until the present day. See 2:23, 11:13, 52:34."
  52,35,"Were they created by none, or were they the creators [of themselves]?",""
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and earth? Rather, they are not certain in faith.",""
  52,37,"Or do they possess the treasures of your Lord, or do they have full control [of everything]?",""
  52,38,"Or do they have a stairway [to the heaven] by which they eavesdrop? Then let those who eavesdrop produce a compelling proof.",""
  52,39,"Or does He have daughters while you have sons<sup>14</sup>?","[14] See footnote 37:149."
  52,40,"Or are you asking them [O Prophet] for a reward so they are overburdened by debt?",""
  52,41,"Or do they have [the knowledge of] the unseen so they are writing it down?",""
  52,42,"Or do they intend a plot [against the Prophet]? But the plot of the disbelievers will rebound against themselves.",""
  52,43,"Or do they have a god other than Allah? Glory be to Allah far above what they associate with Him.",""
  52,44,"If they were to see pieces of the sky falling down<sup>15</sup>, they would still say, “[This is only] a mass of clouds.”","[15] As a sign of the punishment that they requested."
  52,45,"So leave them alone until they encounter their Day in which they will be struck down<sup>16</sup>,","[16] i.e., they will be punished on the Day of Judgment."
  52,46,"the Day their plots will not avail them in the least, nor will they be helped.",""
  52,47,"And for the wrongdoers, there will be another punishment before that<sup>17</sup>, but most of them do not know.","[17] In this world such as famine, droughts, or defeat at the battle, or punishment in the grave."
  52,48,"Be patient [O Prophet] with your Lord’s decree, for indeed you are under Our [Watchful] Eyes. And glorify the praises of your Lord when you rise.",""
  52,49,"And glorify Him at night and when the stars fade away<sup>18</sup>.","[18] i.e., the early hours of the morning when the stars set; the time of the Fajr Prayer."
